7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Crowdin and Lokalise share a solid foundation of core features including Machine Translation, Translation Memory, Glossary, Api Access. Interestingly, both platforms offer nearly identical feature sets. The difference lies more in the implementation quality and depth of each feature rather than feature availability itself. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Crowdin holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Lokalise scores 8/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Crowdin and Lokalise offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Crowdin's free tier and Lokalise's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
