b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Crowdin is best suited for open source projects, game developers, community translation, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Lokalise, meanwhile, shines for development teams, mobile apps, agile teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2009, Crowdin describes itself as \"Collaborative localization platform with crowdsourcing and AI translation.\" Lokalise, established in 2017, positions itself as \"Developer-friendly translation management platform for apps and websites.\" With 8 years between them, Crowdin brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Lokalise offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Lokalise** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Crowdin is a poor choice — far from it. Crowdin excels in its own right, particularly for open source projects and game developers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent developer workflow integration, go with Lokalise. If great crowdsourcing capabilities matters more to you, Crowdin is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
